Q1 (A) – Short Answers

a) ip link set eth0 up command-
It enables (activates) the network interface eth0.
Basically turns the interface ON so it can send/receive data.

b) Detect hidden Wi-Fi networks-
Use tools like:
iw dev
iwlist scan
Wireshark / Kismet
Hidden networks still broadcast signals; only SSID is hidden.

c) Configure router interface with IP-
enable
configure terminal
interface g0/0
ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
no shutdown
exit

d) Purpose of assigning hostname to switch-
Identifies the device in network
Helps in management & troubleshooting
Avoids confusion in multiple devices

f) Ethical hacking-
Legal hacking done to find vulnerabilities
Used for improving security
Done with permission

g) show running-config command-
Displays current active configuration of the device (RAM)
Includes interfaces, IPs, passwords, protocols




Question-2 (B) – Option 1: Ring Topology (C Program)

#include <stdio.h>
int main()
{
int n;
printf("Enter number of computers in ring topology: ");
scanf("%d", &n);
if (n < 2)
{
printf("Ring topology requires at least 2 computers.\n");
return 0;
}
printf("\n----- RING TOPOLOGY -----\n\n");
for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++)
{
printf(" [PC-%d] ", i);
if (i != n)
printf("---");
}
printf("--- [PC-1]");
printf("\n\nAll computers are connected in a closed loop.\n");
return 0;
}






















